2rz.title: Task identification problem
2rz.clickbait: If you have a task-based AGI (Genie) then how do you pinpoint exactly what you want it to do (and not do)?
2rz.text: A subproblem of building a [6w task-directed AGI (genie)] is communicating to the AGI the next task and identifying which outcomes are considered as fulfilling the task.  For the superproblem, see [-2s3].  This seems like primarily a communication problem.  It might have additional constraints associated with, e.g., the AGI being a [102 behaviorist genie].  In the [1fy known-fixed-algorithm] case of AGI, it might be that we don't have much freedom in aligning the AGI's planning capabilities with its task representation, and that we hence need to work with a particular task representation (i.e., we can't just use language to communicate, we need to use labeled training cases).  This is currently a stub page, and is mainly being used as a parent or tag for subproblems.
